<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Off-Canvas</h2>
        <p>
            Off-canvas panels are positioned outside of the viewport and slide in when activated.
        </p>
        <Button DataToggle="offCanvas" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="offCanvasLeft">Toggle Off-canvas</Button>
        <p>
            Off-canvas is a well established mobile pattern for navigation that can also be used to create a responsive sidebar. It can open from any direction, left, right, top, and bottom. There are options to allow the Off-canvas to push your page over or to overlap your page plus a few other neat tricks.
        </p>
        <h2>Setup</h2>
        <p>
            Setting up the Off-canvas only requires two elements! To setup the Off-canvas use <Code Content="PE9mZkNhbnZhcz4="></Code> component.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Off-canvas component also needs a positioning attribute <code>Position</code> to determine which side of the viewport it opens:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>position-left</li>
            <li>position-right</li>
            <li>position-top</li>
            <li>position-bottom</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Also be sure the off-canvas panel has a unique ID so it can be targeted by the click trigger.
        </p>
        <p>
            Example:
        </p>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="PE9mZkNhbnZhcyBQb3NpdGlvbj0icG9zaXRpdmUtbGVmdCIgSWQ9Im9mZkNhbnZhcyI+CjwvT2ZmQ2FudmFzPg==" />

        <p>
            Along with the Off-canvas component, the main content of your page will be housed in its own component with the component <Code Content="PE9mZkNhbnZhc0NvbnRlbnQ+"></Code>. This is where your page content lives.
        </p>

        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="PE9mZkNhbnZhc0NvbnRlbnQ+CiAgPCEtLSBZb3VyIHBhZ2UgY29udGVudCBsaXZlcyBoZXJlIC0tPgo8L09mZkNhbnZhc0NvbnRlbnQ+" />

        <p>
            So putting it all together:
        </p>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="PE9mZkNhbnZhcyBQb3NpdGlvbj0icG9zaXRpb24tbGVmdCIgSWQ9Im9mZkNhbnZhcyI+CiAgPCEtLSBZb3VyIG1lbnUgb3IgT2ZmLWNhbnZhcyBjb250ZW50IGdvZXMgaGVyZSAtLT4KPC9PZmZDYW52YXM+CjxPZmZDYW52YXNDb250ZW50PgogIDwhLS0gWW91ciBwYWdlIGNvbnRlbnQgbGl2ZXMgaGVyZSAtLT4KPC9PZmZDYW52YXNDb250ZW50Pg==" />

        <h2>Wrapper</h2>
        <p>
            You can add an optional wrapper around off-canvas and the content. This hides the vertical (on top/bottom off-canvas) or horizontal (on left/right off-canvas) scrollbars the body will have. Simply use a component <Code Content="PE9mZkNhbnZhc1dyYXBwZXI+"></Code>
        </p>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="" />

        <h2>Click Triggers</h2>
        <p>
            To create a click trigger that opens the panel, add the attribute <Code>data-open</Code> or <Code>DataToggle</Code> to any element. That element will then open or toggle the panel when clicked on. The value of the data attribute should be the ID of the off-canvas.
        </p>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="PEJ1dHRvbiBEYXRhVG9nZ2xlPSJvZmZDYW52YXMiPk9wZW4gTWVudTwvQnV0dG9uPg==" />
        <Button DataToggle="offCanvas1">Open Menu</Button>

        <h2>Close Button</h2>
        <p>
            Foundation's Close component can be used inside the off-canvas to close it.
        </p>
        <HighlightCS Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#5d2b90" HeaderTitle="Razor"
                     Content="PEJ1dHRvbiBDbGFzcz0iY2xvc2UtYnV0dG9uIj4KICA8c3BhbiBhcmlhLWhpZGRlbj0idHJ1ZSI+JnRpbWVzOzwvc3Bhbj4KPC9CdXR0b24+" />

        <h2>Complete Example</h2>
        <p>
            Here's a complete example that can be pasted into the <Code>body</Code> tag of your page. It includes a close button and basic menu styles.
        </p>
