        <p>
            Placing scrollable elements within an off-canvas if <Code>contentScroll: false</Code> is tricky because on touch devices it may become difficult to scroll those elements due to stopped event propagation. There's no continous touch move possible.
        </p>
        <p>
            However you can still achieve this when you add <Code>data-off-canvas-scrollbox</Code> to the scrollable elements. Once you've reached the start/end of a scrollbox (while touch moving) the off-canvas will continue scrolling the off-cannvas element. You can optionally use a wrapper with <Code>data-off-canvas-scrollbox-outer</Code> which gets scrolled instead of the off-canvas element. This is useful when you nest your scrollable elements into other scrollable elements or work with fix heights.
        </p>

